name: Swoop Boeing 737-800 Takeoff and Landing at Calgary Airport
description:
Swoop, Canada's newest airline, is an offshoot of WestJet created to target the ultra-low-cost market. Here's their first aircraft, a 737-800 from WestJet, departing Calgary International Airport on a quick training flight before arriving back again just an hour later. Flights are scheduled to start between Edmonton, Hamilton, Winnipeg, and Abbotsford on June 20th with this and another 737-800, C-FPLS. Enjoy this footage of Swoop in the air, with ATC!

Thanks for watching!
